<HEADLINE> Cambodia's Acting Head of State Oks Election of New PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's acting head of
state Chea Sim Thursday signed an official decree appointing
Foreign Minister Ung Huot as first prime minister to replace
Prince Norodom Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
Chea Sim signed the decree last night, one day after the
parliament's approval of the nomination of Ung Huot as first prime
minister, according to a late night report on the national
television.
</P>
<P>
The decree made the the appointment effective immediately.
</P>
<P>
King Norodom Sihanouk, who was receiving medical treatment in
Beijing, sent a letter to Chea Sim, president of the National
Assembly, on the signing of the decree earlier Thursday. 
</P>
